    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, boil half a kettle, then take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based,<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken breast</strong> to the dish with a pinch of salt and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and cook 4-5 min or until lightly browned</p>",
